# Definition of Done

Before a task is marked done, confirm at least the following:

## Documentation

- Related `FR-*`, `DES-*`, `TEST-*`, and `T-*` items are updated
- The structure and commands in `README.md` are still correct
- Important technical trade-offs are recorded in `docs/adr/` when needed

## Code and Tests

- High-priority requirements have automated verification
- Critical failure scenarios are covered
- Regression tests are updated
- Lint / build / test can run repeatably
- White-box coverage exists for key branches and edge cases
- Performance and security requirements relevant to the current version are verified, or explicitly deferred with justification

## Delivery Quality

- No defaults, empty catches, or fake data are hiding real issues
- New engineering rules are written into `docs/rules/`, not kept only in temporary discussion
- Known risks and unresolved items are explicit instead of hidden
- Material ambiguities were confirmed with the user instead of being silently assumed by the implementer
